      <h1 class="blog-title">What the Family Website Looks Like</h1>

      <p class="blog-meta">The Website &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp; 4 min read</p>

      <div class="blog-body">

        <p>Legacy Odyssey gives your child their own .com domain — a real website where family can open the book in any browser, no app required.</p>

        <p>Here's what they see.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>The Welcome page</h2>

        <p>The first page of the book. It shows your child's name in large type, the hero photo, and the birth details you've enabled — date, time, weight, length, city, hospital. A quote or subtitle you write yourself sits below the name.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>Navigation</h2>

        <p>A left-side navigation bar links to every section of the book with content. Visitors click any section to jump straight to it. Only sections you've filled in appear in the navigation — empty sections stay hidden.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>Section pages</h2>

        <p>Each section has its own page. The design is consistent throughout — warm cream background, gold accents, clean typography. Each page reads as its own part of the book, not as a feed or a grid of thumbnails.</p>

        <p>Month by Month shows a scrollable row of month cards. Each card has the cover photo, the measurements, and the note for that month.</p>

        <p>Celebrations groups entries by year. Each celebration has its title, the written account, and a gallery of photos.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>Password-protected</h2>

        <p>When someone opens your-childs-name.com, they see a password prompt before anything. You set the password. Share it with whoever you want to have access. Nobody sees the book without it.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>Updates in real time</h2>

        <p>Add content in the app or the web editor — it shows on the website immediately. Family following along sees new sections and entries as you add them.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>No app needed to view</h2>

        <p>Family doesn't download anything. No account, no signup. They type the URL, enter the password, and the book opens. Works the same on a phone, a tablet, or a desktop.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>See it yourself</h2>

        <p>The demo is at <a href="https://www.your-childs-name.com">your-childs-name.com</a> — password is <strong>legacy</strong>.</p>

        <div class="blog-cta-box">
          <p><strong>Your child's own .com, their own book.</strong></p>
          <a href="/#pricing" class="btn-primary">Get Started &rarr;</a>
        </div>

        <p class="blog-footer-note"><em>Legacy Odyssey is a digital baby book platform. Every family gets their own private .com, unlimited photo storage, and a Time Vault to seal letters until the day you choose. <a href="https://legacyodyssey.com">Start your baby's site today &rarr;</a></em></p>

